headline: NetApp Stock Tumbles on Revenue Miss and Weak Guidance. Analysts Aren’t Panicking.
summary: As  NetApp  stock slumps following  weaker-than-expected fiscal third-quarter revenue, analysts reiterated their confidence in the data-storage company, arguing that it will continue to perform in-line with peers.  Revenue of $1.64 billion missed the $1.7 billion Wall Street forecast, according to FactSet, while adjusted earnings of $1.91 a share were consistent with analysts’ expectations.  For the current quarter ending in April,  NetApp  said it anticipates revenue of $1.73 billion, missing analysts’ calls for $1.76 billion.
